---
import PresentationLayout from '~/layouts/PresentationLayout.astro';

const metadata = {
  title: 'Agentic Coding: Orchestration',
  description:
    'How to split work between agents, orchestrate specialized teams, and define workflows with skills.',
  ignoreTitleTemplate: false,
};
---

<PresentationLayout metadata={metadata}>
  <!-- Slide 1: Title -->
  <section data-state="title" class="title-slide">
    <h1>Agentic Coding</h1>
    <h2>Orchestration</h2>
  </section>

  <!-- Slide 2: About Me -->
  <section>
    <h2>About Me</h2>
    <div
      style="display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 1.25rem; margin-top: 2rem; max-width: 80%; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;"
    >
      <div style="display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 1rem;">
        <span style="font-size: 1.5rem; min-width: 2rem; text-align: center;">🛠️</span>
        <p style="margin: 0;">15 years of software engineering experience</p>
      </div>
      <div style="display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 1rem;">
        <span style="font-size: 1.5rem; min-width: 2rem; text-align: center;">❤️</span>
        <p style="margin: 0;">I genuinely enjoy coding and building software</p>
      </div>
      <div style="display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 1rem;">
        <span style="font-size: 1.5rem; min-width: 2rem; text-align: center;">🏗️</span>
        <p style="margin: 0;">Currently building <strong>Agewise</strong> as CTO</p>
      </div>
      <div style="display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 1rem;">
        <span style="font-size: 1.5rem; min-width: 2rem; text-align: center;">🤖</span>
        <p style="margin: 0;">Me and my team delegate <strong>99% of coding</strong> to AI agents</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Slide 3: Agenda -->
  <section>
    <h2>Agenda</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>The Context Problem Revisited</li>
      <li>Two Types of Agents</li>
      <li>Basic Orchestration</li>
      <li>Orchestrating a Specialized Team</li>
      <li>Skills as Workflows</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <!-- ==================== Section 1: The Problem ==================== -->

  <!-- Slide 4: The Context Problem — Revisited -->
  <section>
    <h2>The Context Problem — Revisited</h2>
    <p style="color: #a0aec0; margin-bottom: 1.5rem;">
      Previous talk: "one task per session." But what happens when even one task is too big?
    </p>
    <div style="display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; gap: 2rem; margin-top: 1rem;">
      <div
        style="border: 3px solid #e8b4b8; border-radius: 12px; padding: 1.5rem; background: rgba(232, 180, 184, 0.1);"
      >
        <h3 style="margin-bottom: 1rem; color: #e8b4b8;">Without Orchestration</h3>
        <ul style="font-size: 0.95rem; list-style: none; padding: 0;">
          <li style="margin-bottom: 0.6rem;">Developing a bigger feature</li>
          <li style="margin-bottom: 0.6rem;">→ Hit the context limit</li>
          <li style="margin-bottom: 0.6rem;">→ Jump to another session</li>
          <li style="margin-bottom: 0.6rem;">→ Summarize the chat, start over</li>
          <li style="color: #e8b4b8; font-weight: 600;">Context lost each time</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div
        style="border: 3px solid #4ade80; border-radius: 12px; padding: 1.5rem; background: rgba(74, 222, 128, 0.1);"
      >
        <h3 style="margin-bottom: 1rem; color: #4ade80;">With Orchestration</h3>
        <ul style="font-size: 0.95rem; list-style: none; padding: 0;">
          <li style="margin-bottom: 0.6rem;">Main agent stays at high level</li>
          <li style="margin-bottom: 0.6rem;">→ Delegates coding to sub-agents</li>
          <li style="margin-bottom: 0.6rem;">→ Uses much less context</li>
          <li style="margin-bottom: 0.6rem;">→ Orchestrator keeps sharp context</li>
          <li style="color: #4ade80; font-weight: 600;">Knowledge preserved across tasks</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div
      style="border: 2px solid #0ea5c1; border-radius: 12px; padding: 1rem; background: rgba(14, 165, 193, 0.1); margin-top: 1.5rem;"
    >
      <p style="margin: 0; text-align: center; font-size: 0.95rem;">
        Orchestration is the evolution of "one task per session." Now your session can handle many tasks — by
        delegating.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Slide 5: When to Consider Orchestration -->
  <section>
    <h2>When to Consider Orchestration</h2>
    <div style="display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; gap: 1.5rem; margin-top: 1.5rem;">
      <div class="content-box green" style="margin: 0;">
        <span class="content-box-icon">🔄</span>
        <div class="content-box-content">
          <h3>Iterative work</h3>
          <ul style="color: #a0aec0; font-size: 0.85rem; margin: 0.5rem 0 0 0; padding-left: 1.2rem;">
            <li>Many iterations, each needs verification</li>
            <li>Main agent carries knowledge forward</li>
            <li>Context stays clean between iterations</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="content-box" style="margin: 0;">
        <span class="content-box-icon">🧩</span>
        <div class="content-box-content">
          <h3>Different types of work</h3>
          <ul style="color: #a0aec0; font-size: 0.85rem; margin: 0.5rem 0 0 0; padding-left: 1.2rem;">
            <li>Analyze, decide, build backend, frontend, test</li>
            <li>One agent = bloated context</li>
            <li>Specialized agents = focused context</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div
      style="border: 2px solid #0ea5c1; border-radius: 12px; padding: 1rem; background: rgba(14, 165, 193, 0.1); margin-top: 1.25rem;"
    >
      <p style="margin: 0; text-align: center; font-size: 0.95rem;">
        Orchestration is not about parallelism — it is about keeping each agent's context focused and sharp.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ==================== Section 2: Two Types of Agents ==================== -->

  <!-- Slide 6: Section Header -->
  <section data-state="title" class="title-slide">
    <h1 style="font-size: 2.2rem;">Two Types of Agents</h1>
    <h2 style="font-size: 1.3rem; color: #a0aec0; margin-top: 1rem;">The building blocks of orchestration</h2>
  </section>

  <!-- Slide 7: Non-Specialized Agents -->
  <section>
    <h2>Non-Specialized Agents</h2>
    <div style="display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 1.25rem; margin-top: 1.5rem;">
      <div class="content-box">
        <span class="content-box-icon">⚡</span>
        <div class="content-box-content">
          <h3>No configuration needed</h3>
          <p style="color: #a0aec0;">
            Just prompt: <code
              style="background: rgba(14, 165, 193, 0.2); padding: 0.15rem 0.4rem; border-radius: 4px; font-size: 0.9rem;"
              >"implement this test using a sub-agent"</code
            >
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="content-box">
        <span class="content-box-icon">🎛️</span>
        <div class="content-box-content">
          <h3>Model selection</h3>
          <p style="color: #a0aec0;">
            <code
              style="background: rgba(14, 165, 193, 0.2); padding: 0.15rem 0.4rem; border-radius: 4px; font-size: 0.9rem;"
              >"implement this feature using an Opus sub-agent"</code
            >
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="content-box">
        <span class="content-box-icon">⚡</span>
        <div class="content-box-content">
          <h3>Run multiple in parallel</h3>
          <p style="color: #a0aec0;">
            <code
              style="background: rgba(14, 165, 193, 0.2); padding: 0.15rem 0.4rem; border-radius: 4px; font-size: 0.9rem;"
              >"implement auth and notifications using two sub-agents in parallel"</code
            >
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div
      style="border: 2px solid #0ea5c1; border-radius: 12px; padding: 1rem; background: rgba(14, 165, 193, 0.1); margin-top: 1.25rem;"
    >
      <p style="margin: 0; text-align: center; font-size: 0.95rem;">
        Non-specialized agents are your go-to for quick delegation. No setup, no files — just ask.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Slide 8: Specialized Agents -->
  <section>
    <h2>Specialized Agents</h2>
    <div style="display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 1.25rem; margin-top: 1.5rem;">
      <div class="content-box">
        <span class="content-box-icon">📁</span>
        <div class="content-box-content">
          <h3>
            Defined in <code
              style="background: rgba(14, 165, 193, 0.2); padding: 0.15rem 0.4rem; border-radius: 4px; font-size: 1.1rem;"
              >.claude/</code
            > directory
          </h3>
          <p style="color: #a0aec0;">Agent files with special instructions tailored to a specific role</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="content-box">
        <span class="content-box-icon">⚙️</span>
        <div class="content-box-content">
          <h3>Contain</h3>
          <p style="color: #a0aec0;">Workflow rules, guidelines, hooks, skills, and allowed tools</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="content-box">
        <span class="content-box-icon">🎯</span>
        <div class="content-box-content">
          <h3>Repeatable roles with consistent behavior</h3>
          <p style="color: #a0aec0;">
            Same agent, same process, every time. Your backend engineer always follows the same workflow.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div
      style="border: 2px solid #0ea5c1; border-radius: 12px; padding: 1rem; background: rgba(14, 165, 193, 0.1); margin-top: 1.25rem;"
    >
      <p style="margin: 0; text-align: center; font-size: 0.95rem;">
        Specialized agents are your team members. They follow the same process every time.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ==================== Section 3: Basic Orchestration ==================== -->

  <!-- Slide 9: Section Header -->
  <section data-state="title" class="title-slide">
    <h1 style="font-size: 2.2rem;">Basic Orchestration</h1>
    <h2 style="font-size: 1.3rem; color: #a0aec0; margin-top: 1rem;">One orchestrator. Many hands.</h2>
  </section>

  <!-- Slide 10: The Pattern -->
  <section>
    <h2>The Pattern</h2>
    <div
      style="display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr auto 1fr auto 1fr auto 1fr; align-items: center; gap: 0.5rem; margin: 2rem auto; max-width: 95%;"
    >
      <div
        style="background: rgba(14, 165, 193, 0.15); border: 2px solid #0ea5c1; padding: 1rem 0.75rem; border-radius: 10px; text-align: center;"
      >
        <p style="font-size: 0.85rem; font-weight: 700; color: #0ea5c1; margin: 0 0 0.35rem 0;">Plan</p>
        <p style="font-size: 0.75rem; color: #a0aec0; margin: 0;">Eats significant context</p>
      </div>
      <span style="color: #0ea5c1; font-size: 1.5rem;">→</span>
      <div
        style="background: rgba(240, 195, 109, 0.15); border: 2px solid #f0c36d; padding: 1rem 0.75rem; border-radius: 10px; text-align: center;"
      >
        <p style="font-size: 0.85rem; font-weight: 700; color: #f0c36d; margin: 0 0 0.35rem 0;">Delegate</p>
        <p style="font-size: 0.75rem; color: #a0aec0; margin: 0;">Spawn sub-agent</p>
      </div>
      <span style="color: #0ea5c1; font-size: 1.5rem;">→</span>
      <div
        style="background: rgba(74, 222, 128, 0.15); border: 2px solid #4ade80; padding: 1rem 0.75rem; border-radius: 10px; text-align: center;"
      >
        <p style="font-size: 0.85rem; font-weight: 700; color: #4ade80; margin: 0 0 0.35rem 0;">Execute</p>
        <p style="font-size: 0.75rem; color: #a0aec0; margin: 0;">Sub-agent codes</p>
      </div>
      <span style="color: #0ea5c1; font-size: 1.5rem;">→</span>
      <div
        style="background: rgba(14, 165, 193, 0.15); border: 2px solid #0ea5c1; padding: 1rem 0.75rem; border-radius: 10px; text-align: center;"
      >
        <p style="font-size: 0.85rem; font-weight: 700; color: #0ea5c1; margin: 0 0 0.35rem 0;">Result</p>
        <p style="font-size: 0.75rem; color: #a0aec0; margin: 0;">Back to orchestrator</p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <p style="text-align: center; color: #a0aec0; margin-top: 1rem; font-size: 1rem;">
      The main agent's context is not cluttered with the actual implementation. It keeps the high-level picture.
    </p>
    <div
      style="border: 2px solid #0ea5c1; border-radius: 12px; padding: 1rem; background: rgba(14, 165, 193, 0.1); margin-top: 1rem;"
    >
      <p style="margin: 0; text-align: center; font-size: 0.95rem;">
        Your orchestrator thinks. Sub-agents code.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Slide 11: Why It Works — Context Stays Clean -->
  <section>
    <h2>Why It Works — Context Stays Clean</h2>
    <div style="margin-top: 2rem; max-width: 90%; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;">
      <!-- Without orchestration -->
      <p style="font-size: 0.9rem; font-weight: 600; margin-bottom: 0.5rem; color: #e8b4b8;">Without orchestration</p>
      <div
        style="display: flex; border-radius: 12px; overflow: hidden; height: 3rem; font-size: 0.85rem; font-weight: 600; margin-bottom: 1.5rem;"
      >
        <div
          style="flex: 30; background: rgba(14, 165, 193, 0.25); border: 2px solid #0ea5c1; display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: center; border-right: none; border-radius: 12px 0 0 12px;"
        >
          Planning
        </div>
        <div
          style="flex: 50; background: rgba(240, 195, 109, 0.25); border: 2px solid #f0c36d; display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: center; border-right: none;"
        >
          Execution 50%
        </div>
        <div
          style="flex: 20; background: rgba(232, 180, 184, 0.25); border: 2px solid #e8b4b8; display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: center; border-radius: 0 12px 12px 0;"
        >
          Task 2 💥
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- With orchestration -->
      <p style="font-size: 0.9rem; font-weight: 600; margin-bottom: 0.5rem; color: #4ade80;">With orchestration</p>
      <div
        style="display: flex; border-radius: 12px; overflow: hidden; height: 3rem; font-size: 0.85rem; font-weight: 600;"
      >
        <div
          style="flex: 30; background: rgba(14, 165, 193, 0.25); border: 2px solid #0ea5c1; display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: center; border-right: none; border-radius: 12px 0 0 12px;"
        >
          Planning
        </div>
        <div
          style="flex: 5; background: rgba(74, 222, 128, 0.25); border: 2px solid #4ade80; display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: center; border-right: none; font-size: 0.7rem;"
        >
          T1
        </div>
        <div
          style="flex: 5; background: rgba(74, 222, 128, 0.25); border: 2px solid #4ade80; display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: center; border-right: none; font-size: 0.7rem;"
        >
          T2
        </div>
        <div
          style="flex: 5; background: rgba(74, 222, 128, 0.25); border: 2px solid #4ade80; display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: center; border-right: none; font-size: 0.7rem;"
        >
          T3
        </div>
        <div
          style="flex: 5; background: rgba(74, 222, 128, 0.25); border: 2px solid #4ade80; display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: center; border-right: none; font-size: 0.7rem;"
        >
          T4
        </div>
        <div
          style="flex: 50; background: rgba(74, 222, 128, 0.08); border: 2px dashed #4ade80; display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: center; border-radius: 0 12px 12px 0; color: #4ade80;"
        >
          Room for many more ✓
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div
      style="border: 2px solid #0ea5c1; border-radius: 12px; padding: 1rem; background: rgba(14, 165, 193, 0.1); margin-top: 2rem;"
    >
      <p style="margin: 0; text-align: center; font-size: 0.95rem;">
        I use this almost every day when I'm doing feature iterations. I delegate every sub-feature to a new sub-agent so
        that my main session with its knowledge lives longer.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Slide 12: Use Case — Library Migration -->
  <section>
    <h2>Use Case — Library Migration</h2>
    <p style="color: #a0aec0; font-size: 1rem; margin-bottom: 1.25rem;">
      Migrating 10 services to use new library methods. You want full control over each one.
    </p>
    <div style="display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 0.75rem; margin-top: 1rem;">
      <div
        style="display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 1rem; background: rgba(14, 165, 193, 0.1); border: 1px solid #0ea5c1; border-radius: 10px; padding: 1rem 1.25rem;"
      >
        <span
          style="background: #0ea5c1; color: white; font-weight: 700; min-width: 2rem; height: 2rem; border-radius: 50%; display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: center;"
          >1</span
        >
        <p style="margin: 0;">Start with service #1 — <strong>plan the change</strong></p>
      </div>
      <div
        style="display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 1rem; background: rgba(14, 165, 193, 0.1); border: 1px solid #0ea5c1; border-radius: 10px; padding: 1rem 1.25rem;"
      >
        <span
          style="background: #0ea5c1; color: white; font-weight: 700; min-width: 2rem; height: 2rem; border-radius: 50%; display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: center;"
          >2</span
        >
        <p style="margin: 0;"><strong>Delegate the plan</strong> to a sub-agent</p>
      </div>
      <div
        style="display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 1rem; background: rgba(14, 165, 193, 0.1); border: 1px solid #0ea5c1; border-radius: 10px; padding: 1rem 1.25rem;"
      >
        <span
          style="background: #0ea5c1; color: white; font-weight: 700; min-width: 2rem; height: 2rem; border-radius: 50%; display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: center;"
          >3</span
        >
        <p style="margin: 0;">Happy with result → <strong>spawn agent for service #2</strong></p>
      </div>
      <div
        style="display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 1rem; background: rgba(14, 165, 193, 0.1); border: 1px solid #0ea5c1; border-radius: 10px; padding: 1rem 1.25rem;"
      >
        <span
          style="background: #0ea5c1; color: white; font-weight: 700; min-width: 2rem; height: 2rem; border-radius: 50%; display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: center;"
          >4</span
        >
        <p style="margin: 0;">
          Agent uses <strong>all knowledge from migration #1</strong> — no context wasted on implementation
        </p>
      </div>
      <div
        style="display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 1rem; background: rgba(74, 222, 128, 0.1); border: 1px solid #4ade80; border-radius: 10px; padding: 1rem 1.25rem;"
      >
        <span
          style="background: #4ade80; color: #030620; font-weight: 700; min-width: 2rem; height: 2rem; border-radius: 50%; display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: center;"
          >✓</span
        >
        <p style="margin: 0;">Repeat for all remaining services — <strong>single session</strong></p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div
      style="border: 2px solid #0ea5c1; border-radius: 12px; padding: 1rem; background: rgba(14, 165, 193, 0.1); margin-top: 1.25rem;"
    >
      <p style="margin: 0; text-align: center; font-size: 0.95rem;">
        In many cases, you are able to migrate all of the services using a single session.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Slide: Reusing Knowledge Across Iterations -->
  <section>
    <h2>Reusing Knowledge Across Iterations</h2>
    <p style="color: #a0aec0; font-size: 1rem; margin-bottom: 1.25rem;">
      Your orchestrator becomes a knowledge holder — it improves with every iteration.
    </p>
    <div style="display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 0.75rem; margin-top: 1rem;">
      <div
        style="display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 1rem; background: rgba(14, 165, 193, 0.1); border: 1px solid #0ea5c1; border-radius: 10px; padding: 1rem 1.25rem;"
      >
        <span
          style="background: #0ea5c1; color: white; font-weight: 700; min-width: 2rem; height: 2rem; border-radius: 50%; display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: center;"
          >1</span
        >
        <p style="margin: 0;">First iteration — orchestrator learns the <strong>patterns and edge cases</strong></p>
      </div>
      <div
        style="display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 1rem; background: rgba(14, 165, 193, 0.1); border: 1px solid #0ea5c1; border-radius: 10px; padding: 1rem 1.25rem;"
      >
        <span
          style="background: #0ea5c1; color: white; font-weight: 700; min-width: 2rem; height: 2rem; border-radius: 50%; display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: center;"
          >2</span
        >
        <p style="margin: 0;">Second iteration — spawns sub-agent with <strong>better instructions</strong> based on what it learned</p>
      </div>
      <div
        style="display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 1rem; background: rgba(14, 165, 193, 0.1); border: 1px solid #0ea5c1; border-radius: 10px; padding: 1rem 1.25rem;"
      >
        <span
          style="background: #0ea5c1; color: white; font-weight: 700; min-width: 2rem; height: 2rem; border-radius: 50%; display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: center;"
          >3</span
        >
        <p style="margin: 0;">Each next iteration — <strong>more accurate</strong>, because the orchestrator carries all prior knowledge</p>
      </div>
      <div
        style="display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 1rem; background: rgba(74, 222, 128, 0.1); border: 1px solid #4ade80; border-radius: 10px; padding: 1rem 1.25rem;"
      >
        <span
          style="background: #4ade80; color: #030620; font-weight: 700; min-width: 2rem; height: 2rem; border-radius: 50%; display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: center;"
          >✓</span
        >
        <p style="margin: 0;">Sub-agents get a <strong>clean, focused context</strong> — orchestrator keeps the big picture</p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div
      style="border: 2px solid #0ea5c1; border-radius: 12px; padding: 1rem; background: rgba(14, 165, 193, 0.1); margin-top: 1.25rem;"
    >
      <p style="margin: 0; text-align: center; font-size: 0.95rem;">
        The orchestrator does not just delegate — it accumulates knowledge and gets better at delegating with every iteration.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Slide 13: Use Case — Feature Development -->
  <section>
    <h2>Use Case — Feature Development</h2>
    <p style="color: #a0aec0; font-size: 1rem; margin-bottom: 1rem;">
      Building a complex feature with multiple sub-features, iteration by iteration.
    </p>
    <div
      style="display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr auto 1fr auto 1fr auto 1fr; align-items: center; gap: 0.5rem; margin: 1.5rem auto; max-width: 95%;"
    >
      <div
        style="background: rgba(14, 165, 193, 0.15); border: 2px solid #0ea5c1; padding: 0.75rem 0.5rem; border-radius: 10px; text-align: center;"
      >
